# =============================================================================
# wasm4pm drift-monitor descriptor  (AUTO-GENERATED by ggen sync)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Wires the wasm4pm concept-drift detector (pi:Algo_detect_drift, wasm export
# `detect_drift`) as a CONTINUOUS monitor over the predict stage of the chosen
# pipeline. This is the 6th wasm4pm semconv proof: its CONSTRUCT mapping at
# queries/detect-drift.rq turns the detector's JSON output (ADWIN / Page-Hinkley
# change-points) into RDF at wasm4pm runtime.
#
# Driven by queries/extract-pareto-pipeline.rq (the 9 elite rows); filters to the
# predict stage so the monitor binds to the operator actually selected there.
# Drift detection is cross-cutting (it watches the live process the predict-stage
# model scores), so it is emitted as a sibling rule of the predict stage rather
# than competing for the per-stage argmax.
# =============================================================================
@prefix tpot: <https://wasm4pm.dev/tpot#> .
@prefix pi:   <https://wasm4pm.dev/pi#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
{% for row in sparql_results %}{% if row["stage_id"] == "predict" %}
tpot:DriftMonitor_predict a tpot:DriftMonitor ;
    tpot:monitorsStage   "predict" ;
    tpot:monitorsOperator pi:Algo_{{ row["operator_id"] }} ;
    tpot:driftAlgorithm  pi:Algo_detect_drift ;
    tpot:wasmExport      "detect_drift" ;
    tpot:inputFormat     "xes" ;
    tpot:resultMapping   "queries/detect-drift.rq" ;
    tpot:method          "adwin" ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy  tpot:Config_default .
{% endif %}{% endfor %}
